Privacy Policy
"The Website" (www.talkhomeapp.com) and "the App" (Talk Home Calling and Messaging Services) are
                owned and operated by Nowtel Management Limited, part of Talk Home. This policy, together with our
                Terms and Conditions, explains how Talk Home may use information we collect about you when you
                access the Website or the App, as well as your rights over any personal information we hold about
                you. Please read this policy and our Terms and Conditions carefully. By accessing the Website and
                App, you confirm to have understood and agreed to them.
We collect information about you when you:
visit the Website or use the App, and other sites accessible from the
                                            Website or App.
register with and buy products or services on the Website or App.
take part in promotions, competitions, customer surveys and
                                            questionnaires.
contact us for any reason.
We collect personal data in a variety of ways, such as when you visit any of
                                        our websites, download our apps, interact with electronic advertisement, use
                                        our services, make a purchase, complete a survey or competition entry,
                                        contact us and use our customer portal. Examples of this information can be
                                        collected as follows:
Registration and account information: e.g. your phone number, name,
                                            email, profile picture, address and, password, time zone, language,
                                            currency, EU VAT number.
Device and connection information: We collect device and
                                            connection-specific information when you install, access, or use our
                                            services. This includes information like hardware model, operating
                                            system information, app version, browser information, and mobile
                                            network, connection information including phone number, mobile/phone
                                            operator or internet service provider, language and time zone, and IP,
                                            device operations information, and identifiers like device identifiers.
                                            When you install the Talk Home app, you’ll also be asked to allow us
                                            access to your mobile device’s address book. A copy of the phone
                                            numbers, names and, if applicable, account identifiers for our services,
                                            of all your contacts (whether they are a Talk Home customer or not – but
                                            only name, phone number and their account identifier) will be collected
                                            in order for us to provide functionality and administer our services.
Activity and usage information: e.g. information about your use of our
                                            services and other activities in relation to Talk Home, such as
                                            information about when you registered to use our services, how you use
                                            our services, items you purchase, the features you use, your services
                                            settings, the time, frequency, and duration of your activities and
                                            interactions (e.g. the phone numbers and/or other identification details
                                            of the calling and receiving party, the start time, call duration,
                                            messages, mobile money top-ups, delivery notices), log files, and
                                            diagnostic, crash, website, and performance logs and reports.
Location Information: We collect device location information if you use
                                            our location features.
Customer support and social media: If you use our Customer Support
                                            service, interacts with us on our social media channels or in any other
                                            way, we may keep a record of that interaction, including the
                                            correspondence such as copies of emails and your email address.
Behavioural and tracking details: e.g. location data, behavioural
                                            patterns, personal preferences, IP-number, cookie identifiers, unique
                                            identifier of devices you use to access and use the services and our
                                            websites.
Payment information: We collect billing details, name, address, email
                                            address, bank details and other financial information corresponding to
                                            your selected method of payment. However, we will only store name,
                                            address, email and issuing bank (i.e. we don’t store payment card
                                            details).
Collecting your personal information helps Talk Home to better understand what
                                    you need from us. We use your information to:
manage and improve the Website and App.
administer and operate your account.
personalise our services to you.
tell you about important changes to the Website and our services.
understand your shopping behaviour to develop and improve our products and
                                        services.
manage promotions, competitions, customer surveys and questionnaires.
check and verify your identity, and prevent or detect crime.
We may share your personal information across our sister companies so they can
                                    provide you with relevant products and services.
Your personal information is safe with us and will never be released to
                                    companies outside the Talk Home's sister companies for marketing purposes.
If you agree, we may contact you:
with offers and information about Talk Home products or services
with offers and information about partners' products or services
for customer research e.g. to help improve our services
We may contact and communicate with you using several methods including; email,
                                    phone, SMS, app messages, in-app push notifications and any other appropriate
                                    channel.
Push notification preferences should be managed from the iOS or Android
                                        device that you have the App installed on.
Android users can opt out by deselecting the 'Receive Notifications'
                                            tick box in the Talk Home.
iOS users can opt out by going to Settings>Notifications>Talk Home and
                                            then deselect the 'Allow Notifications' toggle.
If you wish to formally opt-out of any of these communications you may:
email
cs-app@talkhome.co.uk
or
contact our Customer Services team on
+44 (0) 333 200 6033
.
In order to comply with new rules, we use a system of classifying the different
                                    types of cookies which we use on the Website, or which may be dropped by third
                                    parties through our websites.
What Are Cookies?
Cookies are small text files stored on your device (computer, tablet, or mobile) when you visit a website.
                                        They help improve your browsing experience by remembering preferences, analyzing site performance, and enabling personalized content.
How We Use Cookies
We use cookies to enhance your experience on the Talk Home website, ensuring seamless navigation and relevant content. The cookies we use fall into four categories:
Strictly Necessary Cookies
- These cookies are essential for the website to function correctly. They enable core functionalities such as security, network management, and accessibility.
                                            Without these cookies, services you request (such as secure log-ins) cannot be provided.
Examples of strictly necessary cookies we use:
Ensuring a secure login process
Maintaining session integrity
Enabling website navigation
Personalisation Cookies
- Personalisation cookies allow us to remember your preferences and settings to provide a customized experience.
                                            These cookies help us tailor the content you see based on your previous interactions with the website.
Examples of personalisation cookies we use:
Analyzing visitor behavior on the website
Identifying and fixing technical issues
Measuring website performance
Performance Cookies
- Performance cookies help us understand how visitors interact with our website by collecting information on page visits, time spent on the site, and any errors encountered.
                                            These insights enable us to improve website performance and user experience.
Examples of performance cookies we use:
Remembering language preferences
Saving user settings for a personalized experience
Marketing Cookies
- Marketing cookies are used to deliver relevant advertisements to users based on their browsing habits.
                                            They help us measure the effectiveness of our marketing campaigns and track user engagement with ads.
Examples of marketing cookies we use:
Displaying relevant ads based on user interests
Measuring ad performance and engagement
Tracking conversions from marketing campaigns
Managing Your Cookie Preferences
You can manage your cookie preferences at any time by adjusting your browser settings or using our website’s cookie consent tool. Most web browsers allow you to:
Accept or reject cookies
Delete stored cookies
Set preferences for certain types of cookies
Please note that disabling certain cookies may affect your experience on our website and limit certain functionalities.
We will never disclose your information to anyone outside the Talk Home and Talk
                                    Home's sister companies except where we have your consent; where we are required
                                    or permitted to do so by law; to other companies who provide a service to us; or
                                    any successors in title to our business.
Whenever we transfer personal information to countries outside the European
                                    Economic Area we will ensure that appropriate security measures are taken.
The Website may contain links to other sites which are outside our control and
                                    not covered by this policy. The operators of these sites may collect information
                                    from you that will be used by them in accordance with their policy, which may
                                    differ from ours.
The Act gives you the right to access information held about you. Your right of
                                    access can be exercised in accordance with the Act. Any access request may be
                                    subject to a fee of £10 to meet our costs in providing you with details of the
                                    information we hold about you.
To delete your account and all associated data with it at any point in time, you will need access to the Talk Home App on your smartphone, available for both Android and iOS.
To delete your account and all associated data, please follow these steps:
Open the App on your smartphone
Tap on the profile icon on the top-left hand side, OR Tap on the hamburger menu icon on the top-right hand side
Navigate to My Account
Tap the pencil icon to edit your profile credentials
Scroll down to the bottom of the screen. Under the "Save” button, you should be able to find the “Delete Account" button.
Enter your PIN. We ask you for your PIN to verify it’s you who’s requesting this action.
Upon successfully entering your PIN, you will be logged out of your account automatically. Please
do not
log back in to your account or the account deletion request will be halted.
We will then take 7 days to process your account deletion. After 7 days, your usage history, billing history, in-app preferences, profile credentials, and other associated settings will be removed from our systems.
In case you have a change of plans and would like to regain access to your account after you’ve submitted an account deletion request, simply log back in within 7 days from the time you submitted the request. This will halt the deletion request and you can continue to use our products and services from your account.
Please note, once your account deletion request is successfully processed, there is no way you can regain access to your information or your account.
Also, once processed, you can not use the same phone number/email address to register for a new account for the next 30 days. We place a temporary hold to ensure our systems have completely removed all instances of any information associated with your credentials.
This policy replaces all previous versions and is correct as of September 2015.
                                    We reserve the right to change the policy at any time
